{"actual_usd":0.12429,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":186,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24300,"reply":"\"I don't know how to make Christianity survive by turning Easter into a pretty symbol.\" *I rub the heel of my thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, watching the morning light catch on the shelf of cooling bowls.* \"If the tomb wasn't truly empty—if Christ wasn't raised in the flesh—then we're not talking about faith at all so much as a consoling story about spring after winter.\"\n\n*I lift one shoulder, slow, not dramatic.* \"Now—symbols, yes. Meanings, yes. New life, absolutely. But those ride on the back of something that happened. My grandmother used to say a cracked mug can stand for endurance all day long, but only if there's an actual mug in your hand.\" *I glance back at you.* \"So for me? Christian faith requires the real thing. Not just that the disciples felt renewed, but that death got answered in history.\"","rolling_24h_usd":84.09870000000001,"run_id":"a95baeb8-5b3e-4f4c-ab28-0af3e360406d"}
